Readme
------

Two independent volume thermal solver in C++.

Uses OpenFOAM built mesh and visualization. Standalone thermal solution.

License
-------

GNU General Public License.

Author
------

Mohamad Hadi Salam.

Requirements
------------

Tested on Ubuntu Linux 18.04 LTS.

GNU C++ compiler g++.

OpenFOAM.

Compiling
---------

Terminal in folder: g++ TwoThermal.cpp -o TwoThermal.bin -pthread -std=c++11

Running
-------

Terminal in folder: ./TwoThermal.bin

Visualizing
-----------

Terminal in folder: paraFoam

In ParaView:

Select / check mark "Volume Fields". Under "Volume Fields", check/tick T1 and T2.

Click Apply.

Select T1/T2 instead of "Solid Color".

Click > "Play".

